-- Russia Equity Movers: Federal Grid, MRSK, RusHydro, Sberbank
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-23T15:41:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/russia-equity-movers-federal-grid-mrsk-rushydro-sberbank.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  lost 3.4
percent to 1,256.55 by the close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index dropped 4.4 percent to 1,264.29.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Federal Grid Co. (FEES RX) slid 9.2 percent to 20.48
kopeks, its lowest level since April 2009. OAO RusHydro (HYDR
RX) tumbled 8.4 percent to 77.31 kopeks, the lowest close since
March 2009. OAO MRSK Holding (MRKH RX) declined 9.7 percent to
1.852 rubles. Russia’s high-voltage power transmission monopoly,
Russia’s largest power producer and the managing company for
interregional power distributors retreated after Interfax news
agency reported that the state may not sell stakes in the
companies.  OAO Sberbank (SBER RX) lost 4.9 percent to 78.75 rubles.
 Russia ’s biggest lender retreated after RIA-Novosti reported the
central bank won’t rush selling its stake in the bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
